#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Explore advanced topics in Spack, including auditing packages and "
"configuration, and verifying installations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:13
msgid "Auditing Packages and Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:15
msgid ""
"The ``spack audit`` command detects potential issues with configuration and "
"packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:19
msgid ""
"For instance, it can detect duplicate external specs in ``packages.yaml``, "
"or the use of non-existing variants in directives. A detailed list of the "
"checks currently implemented for each subcommand can be printed with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:24
msgid ""
"Depending on the use case, users can run the appropriate subcommands to "
"obtain diagnostics. If issues are found, they are reported to stdout:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:27
msgid ""
"% spack audit packages lammps\n"
"PKG-DIRECTIVES: 1 issue found\n"
"1. lammps: wrong variant in \"conflicts\" directive\n"
"    the variant 'adios' does not exist\n"
"    in spack_repo/builtin/packages/lammps/package.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:38
msgid "Verifying Installations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:40
msgid ""
"The ``spack verify`` command can be used to verify the validity of Spack-"
"installed packages any time after installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:44
msgid "``spack verify manifest``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:46
msgid ""
"At installation time, Spack creates a manifest of every file in the "
"installation prefix. For links, Spack tracks the mode, ownership, and "
"destination. For directories, Spack tracks the mode and ownership. For "
"files, Spack tracks the mode, ownership, modification time, hash, and size. "
"The ``spack verify manifest`` command will check, for every file in each "
"package, whether any of those attributes have changed. It will also check "
"for newly added files or deleted files from the installation prefix. Spack "
"can either check all installed packages using the ``-a,--all`` option or "
"accept specs listed on the command line to verify."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:54
msgid ""
"The ``spack verify manifest`` command can also verify that individual files "
"haven't been altered since installation time. If the given file is not in a "
"Spack installation prefix, Spack will report that it is not owned by any "
"package. To check individual files instead of specs, use the ``-f,--files`` "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:58
msgid ""
"Spack installation manifests are included in the tarball signed by Spack for "
"binary package distribution. When installed from a binary package, Spack "
"uses the packaged installation manifest instead of creating one at install "
"time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:61
msgid ""
"The ``spack verify`` command also accepts the ``-l,--local`` option to check "
"only local packages (as opposed to those used transparently from "
"``upstream`` Spack instances) and the ``-j,--json`` option to output machine-"
"readable JSON data for any errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:64
msgid "``spack verify libraries``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:66
msgid ""
"The ``spack verify libraries`` command can be used to verify that packages "
"do not have accidental system dependencies. This command scans the install "
"prefixes of packages for executables and shared libraries, and resolves "
"their needed libraries in their RPATHs. When needed libraries cannot be "
"located, an error is reported. This typically indicates that a package was "
"linked against a system library instead of a library provided by a Spack "
"package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:71
msgid ""
"This verification can also be enabled as a post-install hook by setting "
"``config:shared_linking:missing_library_policy`` to ``error`` or ``warn`` "
"in :ref:`config.yaml <config-yaml>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:76
msgid "Filesystem Requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:78
msgid ""
"By default, Spack needs to be run from a filesystem that supports ``flock`` "
"locking semantics. Nearly all local filesystems and recent versions of NFS "
"support this, but parallel filesystems or NFS volumes may be configured "
"without ``flock`` support enabled. You can determine how your filesystems "
"are mounted with ``mount``. The output for a Lustre filesystem might look "
"like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:83
msgid ""
"$ mount | grep lscratch\n"
"mds1-lnet0@o2ib100:/lsd on /p/lscratchd type lustre (rw,nosuid,lazystatfs,"
"flock)\n"
"mds2-lnet0@o2ib100:/lse on /p/lscratche type lustre (rw,nosuid,lazystatfs,"
"flock)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:89
msgid "Note the ``flock`` option on both Lustre mounts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:91
msgid ""
"If you do not see this or a similar option for your filesystem, you have a "
"few options. First, you can move your Spack installation to a filesystem "
"that supports locking. Second, you could ask your system administrator to "
"enable ``flock`` for your filesystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:95
msgid "If none of those work, you can disable locking in one of two ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:97
msgid ""
"Run Spack with the ``-L`` or ``--disable-locks`` option to disable locks on "
"a call-by-call basis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:98
msgid ""
"Edit :ref:`config.yaml <config-yaml>` and set the ``locks`` option to "
"``false`` to always disable locking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:102
msgid ""
"If you disable locking, concurrent instances of Spack will have no way to "
"avoid stepping on each other. You must ensure that there is only **one** "
"instance of Spack running at a time. Otherwise, Spack may end up with a "
"corrupted database, or you may not be able to see all installed packages "
"when running commands like ``spack find``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:106
msgid ""
"If you are unfortunate enough to run into this situation, you may be able to "
"fix it by running ``spack reindex``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_topics.rst:108
msgid "This issue typically manifests with the error below:"
msgstr ""

